the formula and the total
will update automatically.

87
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:07,580
The great thing about using
cell references is that they

88
00:04:07,580 --> 00:04:09,380
also automatically update when

89
00:04:09,380 --> 00:04:11,325
a formula is copied
to a new cell.

90
00:04:11,325 --> 00:04:13,260
Talk about a time-saver.

91
00:04:13,260 --> 00:04:15,710
Instead of entering
the same formula again

92
00:04:15,710 --> 00:04:18,500
for every new set
of cell references,

93
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:20,420
just copy the formula using

94
00:04:20,420 --> 00:04:24,980
the menu or a keyboard
shortcut like Control plus C.

95
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:29,990
Then paste the formula where
you want to apply it using

96
00:04:29,990 --> 00:04:36,160
Control plus V. And presto!

97
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:37,435
The formula updates

98
00:04:37,435 --> 00:04:39,580
all the new cells and
values correctly.

99
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:43,240
Now let's say you also want
it to find the average sales.

100
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:47,210
For this, you create a new
formula in a different cell.

101
00:04:57,900 --> 00:05:01,900
To group values in a
formula, use parentheses.

102
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:05,110
This lets your spreadsheet know
which values to calculate

103
00:05:05,110 --> 00:05:08,710
together and the order of the
operations to be performed.

104
00:05:08,710 --> 00:05:12,200
For example, open parentheses,

105
